\frac1X\sum_{k=1}^{X-1}\frac{k}Y=\frac1{XY}\sum_{k=1}^{X-1}k=\frac{X(X-1)}{2XY}=\frac{X-1}{2Y}\;.
\frac1X\sum_{k=1}^{Y-1}\frac{k}Y+\sum_{k=Y+1}^X\frac1X=\frac{Y-1}{2X}+\frac{X-Y}X=1-\frac{Y+1}{2X}\;.
